# Visual Identity
- At most TWO typefaces per project (one display, one body)
- ONE accent color max; derive all tones from it
- NO hero cards, NO oversized rounded corners (>12px), NO floating glassmorphism panels
- NO generic gradients — use solid colors with intentional contrast
- NO "AI default" purple/blue gradient vibe

# Spacing System
- Use a 4px or 8px base grid
- Section vertical padding: 80-120px desktop, 48-64px mobile
- Content max-width: 1200px or 1400px centered
- Component internal padding: 16px, 24px, 32px (never random values)

# Typography Hierarchy
- H1: 48-64px, font-weight 700-800, line-height 1.1
- H2: 32-40px, font-weight 600-700, line-height 1.2
- H3: 20-24px, font-weight 600, line-height 1.3
- Body: 16px, font-weight 400, line-height 1.6
- Small/caption: 14px, font-weight 400, line-height 1.5

# Component Patterns
- Buttons: Clear hover/active states, consistent border-radius (6-8px)
- Cards: Subtle border (1px solid) OR light shadow, never both heavy
- Forms: Inline validation, clear error states, accessible labels
- Navigation: Sticky on scroll, mobile hamburger with smooth animation

# Responsive Rules
- Mobile-first breakpoints: 640px, 768px, 1024px, 1280px
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px
- Never hide critical actions behind hover (mobile has no hover)
- Test every component at 375px width before marking done

# Motion & Animation
- Subtle transitions only: 150-300ms, ease-out
- NO bounce effects, NO excessive parallax
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Loading states must be skeleton screens, never spinner-only
